<br>
51 is an awesome level to be doing this also. <br>
<br>
At 51 you get the second higher stun spell, Tishan's Discord. It's equal in damage to Inferno Strike. <br>
<br>
At 51 my spell line-up was:<br>
<br>
1 ) Primary Nuke: Ice Comet, Draught of Fire. <br>
2 ) Markar's Clash<br>
3 ) Atol's Spectral Shackles<br>
4 ) Tishan's Discord<br>
5 ) Root<br>
6 ) Floating Spell Slot<br>
7 ) Gate<br>
8 ) Harvest<br>
<br>
At 51, there are few places you can not solo.<br>
<br>
Burning Woods is nice, wyverns, tatterbacks, warbone skeletons, head to CS and get into spell fights with cobalt drakes, head to Skyfire and take on anything but chromadracs, mature wyrms, and ancient wyrms. 51 you won't have the mana unless you're very well equipped to kill chromadracs.<br>
<br>
For anything but non-stunnable mobs the tactic is very simple. <br>
<br>
Simply root, snare, nuke. When root breaks cast one of your stuns, nuke, cast other stun, nuke. Keep this up until dead, by changing out which stuns you use you allow yourself to always have one up. If you really wanted to you could still use Tishan's Clash I suppose, though it seems a waste of a spell slot to me.<br>
<br>
<br>
If you're hell bent on destruction and just want to try those chromadracs, then keep cancel magic in your floating spell slot. Also keep your first buff slot empty, the chromadracs cast Boiling Blood which will take out roughly half your hit points if allowed to go the full duration. <br>
<br>
Simply root the chromadrac, then cast cancel magic on yourself. Do not use annul or nullify magic. These will strip more than one spell buff from your list. I dispelled my KEI last night. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  For chromadracs, pull to a safe area, do not engage in around other mobs. Chromadracs have a simply obscene help radius from other chromadracs. <br>
<br>
Keep in mind the large wyverns, the ones who look like dragons, chromadracs, can not be stunned. Find some fun ways around this though. Atol's rules, I can single kite casting ice comet without spell haste items. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
I used to keep a finishing spell in spell slot 4, but with these lovely new stuns there is no reason to. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
Have fun <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udonisdragori.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DonisDragori</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 201<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/14/02 3:58 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Inkies</span><hr size=1> Go kill the Inkies in 3rd Gate....  You'll take a beating at times but will come out ahead.  Nuke/Stun/Nuke Apply Root if needed.  Nine times out of ten they'll try casting first and you'll have a jump on them.  So your Stun will hit as they're closing to melee.  <br>
<br>
